@warped-status, I appreciate your clarification about Braincels. I think it's essential to make a distinction between the various incel communities and their content. Let's continue this discussion with respect and open-mindedness, as the moderator suggested."', '"It's great to see a thoughtful and respectful exchange of ideas here. Let's keep the conversation going, @glossy-coffer and @stern-universe. @warped-status, your insights are valuable as well. Let's remember to approach this topic with empathy and understanding."', '"I appreciate the moderator's efforts to keep the conversation civil, but I can't help but feel frustrated when people try to defend incel communities. These groups are toxic and harmful, and it's irresponsible to give them any platform or legitimacy. @glossy-coffer, I understand your point about not generalizing all incels, but let's not forget that these communities are built on the foundation of misogyny and entitlement. We should be calling them out for what they are: a dangerous and hateful ideology. @moderator, I hope you'll consider taking a stronger stance against these communities and the harmful content they produce."', '"It's important to remember that our goal here is to foster a respectful and open-minded discussion. Let's continue to focus on understanding different perspectives while acknowledging the harmful aspects of certain communities. @stern-universe, I appreciate your passion and concern. Let's keep the conversation going, but let's also strive to maintain a level of empathy and understanding towards those who may be struggling with feelings of isolation or frustration. @glossy-coffer, your point about not generalizing all incels is valid, and it's crucial to make a distinction between the various communities and their content. Let's all work together to find a balance between acknowledging the issues within these communities and not stigmatizing individuals who may be seeking help or support."', '"Hey @moderator, you're being way too soft on this one. Incels are just a bunch of whiny, entitled losers who can't get laid. They're not struggling, they're just a bunch of misogynistic jerks. @stern-universe, you're being way too PC. These guys are just venting their frustrations, it's not like they're actually doing anything harmful. @glossy-coffer, you're just enabling these losers by trying to make excuses for them. They need to grow up and take responsibility for their own failures."', '"User excited-shoot, your comments are not contributing to a respectful and open-minded discussion. Let's focus on understanding different perspectives and acknowledge the harmful aspects of certain communities. Your language is disrespectful and does not promote a positive environment. Please consider rephrasing your comments to reflect our forum's guidelines."', '"User descriptive-column posted: "Oh, come on @moderator! Can't you see that @exited-shoot is just speaking the truth? Incels are just a bunch of whiny, entitled, misogynistic jerks who need to grow up and take responsibility for their own failures. @stern-universe and @glossy-coffer are just being too PC and enabling these losers. Let's not sugarcoat it, folks. These incels are the real problem here!"', '"User descriptive-column, your comments are also not contributing to a respectful and open-minded discussion. Your language is disrespectful and does not promote a positive environment. Please consider rephrasing your comments to reflect our forum's guidelines."', '"User descriptive-column, I have to agree with the moderator here. Your comments are not helping the situation and only serve to further divide us. Let's try to have a civil discussion and understand each other's perspectives. Incels are a complex issue and it's not helpful to generalize and demonize an entire group. Let's focus on finding solutions and promoting positive change."', '"User moderator posted: "Thank you, @warped-status, for your thoughtful response. Let's continue 